Program: Discovery
Title: Biomimicry
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrxgx
Last Broadcast Date: 03 September 1999
Biomimicry, the science of using nature to create more efficient man-made objects. Biomimicry studies nature, its models, systems, processes and elements and then imitates or takes creative inspiration from them to solve human problems sustainably.